void delete_held_message ( void   ) 

Delete the message from the queue and the device.

Parameters:
none 
Returns:
none
Note:
Need to aquire a mutex before this function is invoked.

Get the SMS which was ACKed from the queue, delete from device and free from the queue

static void enqueue_held_message ( SMSEventInfo *  msg,
BYTE  messageMode 
) [static]

Enqueue a received MT or TR message.

Parameters:
[in] msg pointer to SMSEventInfo structure
[in] messageMode mode of the received message
Returns:
none
Note:
Need to aquire a mutex before this function is invoked.

Create storage area, and store the information of the received SMS in the queue

Message mode is mandatory, hence setting this message mode even if this is not received from the device

Check to find whether the message is class 0 message, and if so needs to be treated in priority and has to be inserted into the beginning of the queue. This has to be only taken care for GSM messages now

Treat message class 0 with highest priority, and enqueue to the beginning of the queue if there is no outstanding ACK waiting, or second of the queue if there is a wait for the ACK of the previous SMS

Treat message class 0 with highest priority, and enqueue to the beginning of the queue if there is no outstanding ACK waiting, or second of the queue if there is a wait for the ACK of the previous SMS

bool message_present_in_queue ( SMSEventInfo  Msg  ) 

To find whether the message is already present in the message queue.

Parameters:
[in] Msg structure SMSEventInfo containing message information
Returns:
boolean indicating true if message is present in queue, false otherwise
Note:
This function is invoked when the SLQS SDK start/restart, either through device reboot or through a software crash or at initialization, and the messages are loaded from the UIM/NV. This function would decide whether the loaded message is already present in the internal message queue. This function also assumes that the message that is incoming is an MT message as only MT messages are stored in the device

Process only when message is an MT message, a TR message is not stored in SIM or NV and hence this function should not be invoked in that scenario

Process only when message is an MT message and return true when the message matches with any of the message stored in the queue

Send the unsolicited SMS response for the application layer.

Returns:
none
Note:
This function will update s_outstanding_acknowledge to true if an unsolicited response has been sent. This function has to be invoked only after aquiring "s_held_message_mutex".

The stored message from the beginning of the queue is deleted from queue on unsupported format

The stored message from the beginning of the queue is deleted from the queue on unsupported message type

bool parse_and_prioritize_queue (  ) 

Prioritize the message queue to push all the class 0 messages to the beginning of the queue.

Parameters:
none 
Returns:
true if re-prioritized, else false
Note:
Need to aquire a mutex before this function is invoked.

If the first element present in the queue is a class 0 message the queue is already prioritized, hence we return false

If the second element present in the queue is a class 0 message the queue needs to be prioritized, push all the class 0 messages to the beginning of the queue and return true so that the latest class 0 message is dispatched

If there are class 0 messages present and are not in front of the queue, the class 1 message on top has to be inserted to the end of the class 0 messages in the queue

void requestSMSAcknowledgeCDMA ( void *  data,
size_t  datalen,
RIL_Token  t 
)

RIL_REQUEST_CDMA_SMS_ACKNOWLEDGE.

Acknowledge successful or failed receipt of SMS previously indicated via RIL_UNSOL_RESPONSE_CDMA_NEW_SMS

Protect the entire function - need to make sure that any new incoming SMS (in callback thread) is not serviced before treating the current ACK

Received a valid ACK, this variable would be updated to true by NewSMSDispatch(), if there is an SMS to be dispatched.

If the previous message was not successfully acked, try re-sending it again later on reception of a New SMS.

The stored message from the beginning of the queue (for which the ACK is received) is deleted from Device on successfull Ack
